This directory is for sharing bash themes. To use a theme, just source it in
your custom/*.bash script. For example:

    source $BASH/custom/verbose.bash


Theme-related settings could include:

PS1                 What to display for the command prompt
PROMPT_COMMAND      Command(s) to execute prior to issuing a bash prompt
LS_COLORS           Usually set by running "eval `dircolors -b $HOME/.dir_colors`"


To quickly view a sample of all of the themes, try this: (TODO)


NOTE: These may be useful in PS1:
    \a      an ASCII bell character (07)
    \d      the date in "Weekday Month Date" format
    \e      an ASCII escape character (033)
    \h      the hostname up to the first `.'
    \H      the hostname
    \j      the number of jobs currently managed by the shell
    \l      the basename of the shell's terminal device
    \n      newline
    \r      carriage return
    \t      the current time in 24-hour HH:MM:SS format
    \T      the current time in 12-hour HH:MM:SS format
    \@      the current time in 12-hour am/pm format
    \u      the username of the current user
    \v      the version of bash (e.g., 2.00)
    \V      the release of bash, version + patchlevel
    \w      the current working directory
    \W      the basename of the current working dir
    \!      the history number of this command
    \#      the command number of this command
    \$      if the effective UID is 0, a #, otherwise a $
    \\      a backslash

